The paper focuses on the phenomenon of adversarial examples in computer vision, specifically for offline handwritten signature verification systems. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the security implications of adversarial examples, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The experiments conducted in the paper involve machine learning classifiers, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves feature extraction, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper evaluates the impact of countermeasures, which suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible sub-category as well.
